  "description": "Maggie's Garden continues Gardener & Son's commitment to purpose-driven, regenerative, and biophilic garden design -- creating a living landscape that restores habitat, supports biodiversity, and offers daily beauty and calm. Designed as a wild native meadow with cottage-style softness, the garden provides food, shelter, and shade for local fauna while softening the visual edge of the driveway and concealing the power pole. High-density planting at 6-10 plants per m2 across a 3x8m front garden. It also welcomes people, children, neighbours, and passers-by into a space that feels generous, natural, and alive.",
